# Payload Migration Baseline Workflow

- Follow [branch-workflow](branch-workflow.mdc): ship migration work on a feature branch, PR into `develop` (no direct push to `develop`); do not open pull requests into `main` except `develop` → `main`.
- Treat baseline rollouts as controlled infra changes.
- Freeze schema-changing edits during baseline rollout windows.
- For existing dev-pushed databases, do not run giant autogenerated full-schema migrations.
- Use a baseline anchor migration to establish shared migration history.
- Mark baseline as applied for already-provisioned databases via migration tracking records.
- Verify each environment with `payload migrate:status` before unfreezing schema edits.
- After baseline, use incremental migrations only: `payload migrate:create` -> review SQL -> `payload migrate`.
